Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.54,0:03:45.33,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon pages and pages of entries
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.73,0:03:49.47,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,We've put down all our emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.97,0:03:52.76,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,But now I've hit a writer's block
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.01,0:03:56.73,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to finish this page anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.98,0:03:59.92,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Putting a bookmark in my diary
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.54,0:04:04.96,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I go out to ride the bike we found in the dumpster
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:08.12,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to our secret place
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:12.46,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Where we piled up our bricks of memories
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.26,0:04:17.72,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Run up the hill, where we can see the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:22.26,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Where we can see the sky so fearfully blue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:25.48,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,With cider in my right hand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:29.99,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,My other hand helps me search for you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:34.11,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You used to come find me way back when
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:37.80,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You used to demand me of so much more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:44.58,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You're both still standing right by my side
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:52.36,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet why do I pray to see you both again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.56,0:05:00.47,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be something off with me
